Group settings with section headers (RECORDINGS, FILTERS, APPLICATION) i wioll


--------------------------------------------
in the RECORDINGS sub option add

Audio Format (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Audio Format"
Options:

8-bit PCM
16-bit PCM
24-bit PCM (float)


Default: 16-bit PCM (pre-selected with radio button)
Show current selection below the setting title in the main settings screen
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)
Include "Cancel" button to dismiss without changes
Automatically apply and dismiss on selection

--------------------------------------------

always in the RECORDINGS sub option  add
Recordings Folder

Display current storage path
Allow user to select/change the folder location
Default path: /storage/emulated/0/Android/data/com.github.axet.audiorecorder/files
Should support custom folder selection via file picker


Audio Format (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Audio Format"
Options:

8-bit PCM
16-bit PCM
24-bit PCM (float)


Default: 16-bit PCM (pre-selected with radio button)
Show current selection below the setting title in the main settings screen
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)
Include "Cancel" button to dismiss without changes
Automatically apply and dismiss on selection


Recording Source (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Recording Source"
Options:

Mic
Bluetooth
Internal Audio
Camcorder
Voice Communication
Voice Recognition


Default: Mic (pre-selected with radio button)
Show current selection below the setting title
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)
Include "Cancel" button to dismiss without changes
Show additional warning dialog after selecting "Internal Audio" or "Bluetooth" (see Special Handling section)


Sample Rate (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Sample Rate"
Options:

8 kHz
16 kHz (default)
22.05 kHz
44.1 kHz
48 kHz


Default: 16 kHz
Show current selection with "(default)" text if applicable
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)


Encoding (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Encoding"
Options:

.ogg (Vorbis)
.mp3
.wav
.m4a
.flac


Default: .ogg
Show current selection below the setting title
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)


Audio Channels (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Audio Channels"
Options:

Mono (default)
Stereo


Default: Mono
Show current selection with "(default)" text if applicable
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)


Filename Format

Filename Format (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Filename Format"
Options:

2025-11-20 08.09.09.ogg (Human-readable with spaces)
1763644149.ogg (Unix timestamp)
20251120T080909.ogg (ISO 8601 basic format)
20251120T130909Z.ogg (ISO 8601 UTC format)
-----------------------------------------------------------

FILTERS Section

Voice Filter (Toggle Switch)

Description: "Bandpass Voice Filter"
Default: OFF


Recording Volume (Slider)

Range: 0-200%
Default: 100%
Display current percentage


Skip Silence (Toggle Switch)

Description: "Skip Silence while recording"
Default: OFF



APPLICATION Section

Encoding on the Fly (Toggle Switch)

Description: "Enabling encoding on the fly disables editing, and crash recovery"
Default: OFF


Pause During a Call (Toggle Switch)

Description: "Stop recording on answering and continue on hangup"
Default: ON (enabled in screenshot)


Silent Mode (Toggle Switch)

Description: "Enable 'silent mode' during recording"
Default: OFF


Lockscreen Controls (Toggle Switch)

Description: "Show the controls when the phone is locked"
Default: OFF


Application Theme (List Dialog/Modal)

Clicking opens a modal dialog with radio button list
Dialog title: "Application Theme"
Options:

Theme White
Theme Dark
System Default


Default: Theme White
Use AlertDialog with single choice items (radio buttons)
